      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8846" identifier="1751f57ca94f5a1049bbd2d229c99266">
        <source>Check each letter of the input string “cards” (use a loop to iterate
the number of letters in the input) starting from the last letter.</source>
        <target>crwdns8846:0crwdne8846:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/ul/li[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8847" identifier="9e4ef4eca23ab5da5da7b294faccceca">
        <source>If it’s ‘W’ add the corresponding number of dots (1 for the last
letter, 2 for the second to last letter and so on) to the “total
number of dots”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8847:0crwdne8847:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/ul/li[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8848" identifier="63a272a6f574771cf8715c9943864da2">
        <source>Display the “total number of dots” as the output.</source>
        <target>crwdns8848:0crwdne8848:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/ul/li[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8849" identifier="ee8c64e6eaf438b3f28a77e2ada15049">
        <source>“index” and set its value to the number of letters in the input.
Use this variable to access a letter at the “index” position in the
string.</source>
        <target>crwdns8849:0crwdne8849:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li/ul/li[4]</note>
